item.title: Ana add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "What really knocks me out is a book that, when you're all done reading it, you wish the author that wrote it was a terrific friend of yours and you could call him up on the phone whenever you felt like it. That doesn't happen much, though." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Ana add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I love you to pieces, distraction, etc." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Ana add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "Ask her if she still keeps all her kings in the back row." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Ana add a quote by J. D. Salinger
item.description: "There isn’t a nightclub in the world that you can sit in for a long time unless you can at least buy some liquor and get drunk. Or unless you’re with some girl that really knocks you out." -- J. D. Salinger

item.title: Ana add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "Her joke of a name aside, her general unprettiness aside, she was, in terms of permanently memorable, immoderately perceptive, small-area faces, a stunning and final girl." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Ana add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I don't exactly know what I mean by that, but I mean it." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Ana add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "She wrote to him fairly regularly, from a paradise of triple exclamation points and inaccurate observations." -- J.D. Salinger
